  "audio_design_principles": {
    "walter_murch_rule": "The sound that does NOT exist is often more powerful than the sound that does. T-Rex territory uses silence as the primary sound design tool.",
    "rdr2_principle": "Music the player never consciously notices but that changes what they feel is the peak of interactive composition.",
    "spatial_audio_strategy": "All zones use attenuation falloff — player hears the zone before they see it. Sound is the first sense that tells them where they are.",
    "subsonic_design": "T-Rex territory uses 18-22Hz LFE pulses below conscious hearing threshold. Player feels unease without knowing why.",
